      "notes": "The Uley family includes both parts of the Clearwater family and the Lahote family, as they're all related. \n\nOne of the challenges here is to fill in the gaps for Paul's family, as he's descended from Ruth and Gene Lahote, but there's a two generation gap there. So I'm slowly filling that in. The circumstances there are going to be interesting, because I'm certain it's either mentioned or heavily implied that Paul's home life is questionable.\n\nI also took some liberties with Sam's history- his parents are divorced, and based on the tree, you can maybe guess why. In Dreaming, Joshua Uley has one confirmed daughter outside of his marriage and two suspected daughters. I also included Sam's second cousins, the Zhelenov/Grays. The Zelenovs are of Russian descent, as a call back to the Russian ship that probably made first contact with the Quileute, and then I decided I was going to give Sam more family."
    },
